WEBVTT

00:02.794 --> 00:04.170
NARRATOR:
Two weeks ago, an invisible dome

00:04.338 --> 00:06.374
crashed down on Chester's Mill,

00:06.548 --> 00:08.459
cutting us off
from the rest of the world.

00:08.634 --> 00:10.966
Why the dome is here
or What mysteries lie ahead,

00:11.136 --> 00:14.549
we still don 't know.
Every day, it tests our limits,

00:14.723 --> 00:17.305
bringing out the best
and the worst in us.

00:19.019 --> 00:21.180
Some say
we 7/ be stuck here forever.

00:21.980 --> 00:25.723
But we will never stop ﬁghting
to ﬁnd a way out.

00:27.194 --> 00:28.650
[GASPS, THEN SCREAMS]

00:29.571 --> 00:30.811
Angie is dead.

00:31.490 --> 00:32.525
JIM:
Oh, my Lord.

00:32.699 --> 00:34.030
BARBIE:
You point the finger at me?

00:34.201 --> 00:36.533
-Neither of us would do this.
-So then who would?

00:36.703 --> 00:39.536
JUNIOR: Is it possible to love someone
so much that you'd hurt them?

00:39.706 --> 00:42.994
But you'd never do anything violent
to the person you loved, would you?

00:43.168 --> 00:45.284
JULIA:
First we lose Linda. Now Angie.

00:45.462 --> 00:47.202
I thought the dome
was supposed to protect us.

00:47.381 --> 00:49.667
No, it's up to us
to protect each other.

00:49.841 --> 00:53.083
There are too many people in here
for our limited resources.

00:53.262 --> 00:54.502
We can't all survive.

00:54.680 --> 00:56.341
NORRIE: Who is she?
JOE: Hey, what's your name?

00:56.515 --> 00:58.005
It was the girl we saw in the woods.

00:58.183 --> 00:59.889
We found her bloody shoe print
at the school.

01:00.060 --> 01:02.016
JULIA: This looks like her.
Pauline drew this?

01:02.187 --> 01:03.302
Twenty years ago.

01:13.532 --> 01:14.863
I was just...

01:17.035 --> 01:18.946
-...Iooking.
-For what?

01:20.080 --> 01:21.115
Reminders.

01:25.586 --> 01:27.872
Your license
says you're from Zenith.

01:28.463 --> 01:30.670
You're not from here?

01:31.508 --> 01:34.250
- Where are you from?
- I don't know.

01:34.428 --> 01:36.168
Are you interrogating her?

01:37.389 --> 01:39.129
No, I'm--

01:41.810 --> 01:43.675
I'm just trying to figure out who she is,
okay?

01:43.854 --> 01:46.061
We don't even know her name.

01:46.773 --> 01:48.229
Try to be patient with her.

01:48.400 --> 01:51.642
I'm sorry, I'm not buying
this whole little baby bird act.

01:51.820 --> 01:53.560
- It's not an act.
- Are you sure about that?

01:53.739 --> 01:57.106
Because I just came in here
and found her going through my stuff.

01:58.827 --> 02:03.742
Ijust want you to be more careful
about bringing strays into our house.

02:04.207 --> 02:07.950
Well, let's not forget the last stray
that I brought in was you.

02:11.381 --> 02:12.837
I'm gonna head down to the diner.

02:13.008 --> 02:16.375
Jim's mandatory citizen registration?

02:26.271 --> 02:28.102
Can I come with you?

02:28.273 --> 02:30.104
Of course you can.

02:30.692 --> 02:33.934
Do you think someone
will recognize me?

02:36.156 --> 02:38.272
We'll figure it out, sweetie.

02:42.204 --> 02:45.822
[THE BONES OF J.R. JONES'
"TICKET HOME" PLAYING ON RADIO]

02:48.126 --> 02:49.161
What's that scent?

02:50.087 --> 02:52.078
It's a dram of cassia oil.

02:52.255 --> 02:53.586
It's nice, huh?

02:53.757 --> 02:56.123
Could you make a cologne?

02:56.301 --> 02:58.132
For you? Yeah.

02:58.303 --> 03:01.010
- You got a big date?
- It's been nine years since, uh...

03:01.181 --> 03:03.137
- Pauline passed.
- Yeah.

03:03.308 --> 03:05.970
Yeah, I still think about her
every day.

03:07.604 --> 03:12.689
So I was, uh, grateful
for your support during that time.

03:12.859 --> 03:16.443
It couldn't have been easy,
given your history with her.

03:17.322 --> 03:19.699
Better man won that battle, Jim.

03:19.866 --> 03:22.118
Who's this lucky lady?

03:22.619 --> 03:23.904
Rebecca Pine.

03:24.079 --> 03:26.821
She's a science teacher
at the high school.

03:26.998 --> 03:28.124
We've been working together.

03:28.750 --> 03:31.958
Let's just say there's something
interesting about her.

03:33.839 --> 03:37.002
If you want, I could whip up
a fragrance for you, Jim,

03:37.175 --> 03:39.006
and get your pheromones kicking.

03:39.177 --> 03:40.337
I'd appreciate that, Lyle.

03:43.515 --> 03:46.507
None of that, uh, cassia oil though.

03:47.394 --> 03:48.509
Comes off a bit feminine.

03:49.312 --> 03:50.347
[CHUCKLES]

03:50.856 --> 03:52.096
What are you smiling about?

03:53.024 --> 03:55.811
I don't know,
just something about the day

03:56.862 --> 03:58.227
seems auspicious.

03:58.405 --> 04:00.987
I'll expect you later at the Sweetbriar
for the registration.

04:01.658 --> 04:03.159
Yeah.

04:03.326 --> 04:05.578
Yeah, see you down there.

04:05.746 --> 04:09.034
JIM: Answer every question
to the best of your knowledge.

04:09.249 --> 04:11.365
This survey will provide us
with the proper information

04:11.543 --> 04:13.625
to get everyone
the resources they need.

04:20.093 --> 04:21.754
Should I look around?

04:21.928 --> 04:24.385
Yes. I'll be right here.

04:28.185 --> 04:30.141
Has that girl remembered anything
about Angie yet?

04:30.312 --> 04:31.347
Don't worry.

04:31.521 --> 04:33.182
We're gonna find the person
who killed her.

04:33.356 --> 04:36.063
Also, there were four hands
a couple days ago.

04:36.234 --> 04:38.270
Now with my sister gone,
there's only three.

04:38.445 --> 04:39.605
Would the dome let her die?

04:40.614 --> 04:42.104
What if we were wrong?

04:42.282 --> 04:44.898
-And the dome isn't here to protect us?
-I don't know.

04:45.410 --> 04:48.573
If you don't know, who will?

04:48.955 --> 04:50.911
I noticed you didn't have one of these.

04:51.082 --> 04:54.074
- Thank you.
- I'm just helping out.

04:54.252 --> 04:55.913
REBECCA:
Joe?

04:56.087 --> 04:57.793
Hi. I need a favor.

04:57.964 --> 05:00.626
Can you open up the project room
and make sure it's prepped?

05:00.801 --> 05:03.383
Remember that windmill project we did
on alternative energy?

05:03.553 --> 05:06.295
- I still have the specs on my tablet.
- Great, bring it.

05:06.473 --> 05:09.431
We're gonna be replicating
the concept on a much larger scale

05:09.601 --> 05:11.592
to generate electricity for the town.

05:11.770 --> 05:13.135
Cool.

05:13.438 --> 05:16.430
- You can take your friend.
- I don't go to school here.

05:16.608 --> 05:20.192
Well, everyone between 14 and 18
is expected to participate.

05:20.362 --> 05:24.275
And there goes the last perk
of dome-living.

05:24.449 --> 05:26.155
JULIA:
Do you recognize anyone?

05:26.326 --> 05:30.615
- You can help out too.
- No. She stays with me.

05:30.789 --> 05:32.996
- Help with what?
- An experiment.

05:34.084 --> 05:36.746
It's okay. I'd like to help.

05:43.134 --> 05:44.965
Look out for her.

05:46.054 --> 05:49.467
So you're really embracing
your new responsibilities, aren't you?

05:49.641 --> 05:53.600
Well, I serve at the pleasure
of our councilman.

05:53.770 --> 05:55.681
Please fill that out.

06:02.070 --> 06:05.608
Why torture yourself
if you don't know?

06:05.907 --> 06:08.114
Angie's bracelet was under my cot.

06:10.495 --> 06:12.281
You loved her, right?

06:13.164 --> 06:14.495
More than anything.

06:15.083 --> 06:16.584
Do you really think

06:16.751 --> 06:20.494
you could have killed the person
you loved more than anything?

06:21.214 --> 06:22.670
No.

06:22.841 --> 06:24.547
I don't know.

06:24.843 --> 06:26.879
Why can't--?
Why can't I remember?

06:34.519 --> 06:36.976
The night Angie was killed,
you said you blacked out.

06:37.147 --> 06:39.934
Those were the words you used.

06:40.108 --> 06:43.771
I don't know what this means--
It might not mean anything.

06:44.112 --> 06:46.945
--but your mom,
she had blackouts too.

06:47.115 --> 06:49.356
Fugue states, the doctor called them.

06:49.534 --> 06:52.116
Dissociative or something like that.

06:52.287 --> 06:54.869
What would happen to her when
she had them? Would she get violent?

06:55.040 --> 06:56.746
What's important
is that sometimes afterward,

06:56.917 --> 06:59.124
she'd go back to where she
was when the blackout hit.

06:59.294 --> 07:01.034
And she would get these flashes.

07:01.212 --> 07:03.669
Glimpses, little bits of memory
coming back.

07:04.925 --> 07:08.338
So I should go back
to where I found Angie.

07:08.511 --> 07:09.967
Maybe something will come back.

07:10.597 --> 07:11.632
Hey, James.

07:12.599 --> 07:15.056
No matter what,
you and me are family.

07:15.560 --> 07:16.640
We'll figure this out.

07:24.152 --> 07:25.187
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

07:29.783 --> 07:32.900
All right, folks. Grab any receptacle
you can find, folks. Let's go.

07:33.078 --> 07:34.284
Precipitation's scarce.

07:34.454 --> 07:37.946
Let's collect as much drinkable water
as we can.

07:38.124 --> 07:40.035
She's a little bossy, don't you think?

07:41.127 --> 07:42.867
Wait.

07:51.429 --> 07:53.385
It's raining blood.

08:16.830 --> 08:18.036
It can't be blood, can it?

08:18.873 --> 08:21.410
I don't think it's cherry Kool—Aid.

08:22.419 --> 08:23.579
[SKIN SIZZLES,
THEN GIRL SCREAMS]

08:23.753 --> 08:26.540
GIRL: It burns.
- Let's go wash it off. Come on.

08:28.383 --> 08:31.875
All right, listen up, everybody.
Stay calm and stay inside.

08:32.053 --> 08:35.386
Don't leave the cafe
till the rain stops, all right?

08:35.557 --> 08:36.546
- Jim.
- Yeah?

08:36.725 --> 08:39.057
You know what this is about,
don't you?

08:39.728 --> 08:40.843
The ten plagues.

08:41.438 --> 08:44.726
Lyle, don't start getting all biblical
on me now, okay?

08:44.899 --> 08:47.561
But that swarm the other day,
that may have as well been locusts.

08:47.736 --> 08:49.943
Butterflies are not locusts, Lyle.

08:50.113 --> 08:52.320
Jim, it's like three plagues
rolled into one.

08:52.490 --> 08:56.199
Storm of fire, boils,
and water turns to blood.

08:56.369 --> 08:57.404
It's not blood.

08:57.912 --> 08:58.947
How do you know?

08:59.122 --> 09:00.703
Well, blood doesn't burn.

09:00.874 --> 09:03.490
But it doesn't usually fall
out of the sky either, but take a look.

09:03.668 --> 09:06.205
There was a red rain phenomenon
in India a decade ago.

09:06.379 --> 09:09.246
It was caused by spores
from an abnormal algae bloom.

09:09.924 --> 09:12.791
I'm looking at scripture to tell me
what this is. What are you looking at?

09:13.970 --> 09:17.588
Science,
like when the dome magnetized,

09:17.766 --> 09:19.427
or the crops were infested.

09:20.018 --> 09:23.226
So you'll solve everything, huh?
You and science?

09:23.396 --> 09:25.432
Or go down trying, okay.

09:25.607 --> 09:26.847
Um, I collected a sample.

09:27.192 --> 09:29.433
I can analyze it and look for a way
to neutralize the acidity.

09:29.611 --> 09:30.646
[DOOR OPENS]

09:30.820 --> 09:32.776
SAM: Little help.
JULIA: Put her down over there.

09:32.947 --> 09:35.780
I'm glad you're here. We've got people
who might need medical attention.

09:35.950 --> 09:38.942
- Burning skin?
- Yup, everybody's stable. Excuse me.

09:39.120 --> 09:40.781
We should gO back out.

09:40.955 --> 09:42.491
I saw other people stranded
out there.

09:42.665 --> 09:45.156
There's an ambulance at med center.
That's close by.

09:45.335 --> 09:47.075
Cover up. Let's go.

09:49.631 --> 09:50.746
NORRIE:
What is it?

09:50.924 --> 09:52.460
JOE:
It's just...

09:57.597 --> 09:58.632
What are you doing here?

09:58.807 --> 10:00.468
- Homework.
- What about you?

10:01.226 --> 10:02.261
Same.

10:03.603 --> 10:05.468
Anyways, I'm gonna take Off now.

10:05.980 --> 10:08.107
- You can't.
- Why not?

10:09.609 --> 10:11.474
You haven't been outside for a while,
have you?

10:18.827 --> 10:20.488
Apocalypse.

10:21.037 --> 10:22.652
- What did you say?
- The apocalypse,

10:22.831 --> 10:24.662
what Lyle was talking about.

10:24.833 --> 10:25.948
You believe in that?

10:26.584 --> 10:29.621
I believe in the original definition
Of apocalypse.

10:29.796 --> 10:34.039
It's Greek. TO uncover or reveal.

10:34.217 --> 10:38.256
That's what crises do.
They reveal character.

10:38.429 --> 10:40.465
Strength.

10:42.809 --> 10:44.390
Or not.

10:45.478 --> 10:46.809
You think we're being tested?

10:48.148 --> 10:52.061
I mean the rain, infestation,
everything.

10:52.527 --> 10:56.440
You think it's a test from the dome?

10:56.614 --> 10:58.195
TO see whether I'm worthy?

10:58.366 --> 10:59.697
Jim, we can solve this.

11:00.243 --> 11:03.110
The red algae must have come from
the lake which could've gotten toxified

11:03.288 --> 11:04.869
from everything
we've been dumping in it.

11:05.039 --> 11:09.874
Not to mention, um, pesticides,
trash fires, trapped exhaust from cars.

11:10.044 --> 11:11.659
The town's
an environmental horror show.

11:12.422 --> 11:14.208
And we're stuck inside.

11:15.049 --> 11:17.836
Believe in me, and I will believe in you.

11:20.305 --> 11:22.887
Science and faith, huh?

11:24.601 --> 11:25.841
LOOk out!

11:26.019 --> 11:27.054
[TIRES SCREECHING]

11:34.903 --> 11:35.938
[JIM GRUNTS]

11:41.451 --> 11:42.486
[GRUNTING]

11:51.544 --> 11:53.830
Is he Okay?

11:55.340 --> 11:57.547
I don't think he's ever been Okay.

11:59.928 --> 12:01.668
Are you Okay?

12:01.846 --> 12:04.679
Yeah. Yeah, I'm fine.

12:06.851 --> 12:09.763
- Will you give me a hand?
- I didn't hear a bell.

12:09.938 --> 12:12.270
Come on, Norrie,
there's an extra tablet on the shelf.

12:12.440 --> 12:15.273
We gotta look up the specs
on the windmill.

12:29.958 --> 12:31.073
Oh, my God.

12:32.794 --> 12:33.829
What is it?

12:34.587 --> 12:35.622
E-mail.

12:38.299 --> 12:39.584
I'm getting e-mail.

12:43.179 --> 12:46.342
This is Big Jim on Motton Road.

12:46.516 --> 12:47.596
Across from Killian's.

12:48.559 --> 12:50.345
Send help.

12:54.691 --> 12:55.931
NORRIE:
LOOk at this.

12:56.109 --> 12:58.976
We're super-trendy in Twitter-Land.

12:59.904 --> 13:01.735
Who's houndsofdiana?

13:01.906 --> 13:02.986
They're all over my page.

13:04.826 --> 13:06.282
Are they messages?

13:06.452 --> 13:07.487
Yeah.

13:07.662 --> 13:09.198
First since the dome came down.

13:09.831 --> 13:12.664
I don't know how the signal's
getting through though.

13:16.004 --> 13:17.039
It's from my dad.

13:18.089 --> 13:19.374
GIRL:
What does it say?

13:21.843 --> 13:24.380
JOE: "Your mother and I pray every
day that we'll get to see you soon.

13:25.138 --> 13:27.504
In the meantime,
stay safe and be smart.

13:27.682 --> 13:30.424
You're the man Of the house now.

13:32.478 --> 13:34.184
Take care Of your sister."

13:38.443 --> 13:40.479
What do I even say?

13:43.323 --> 13:46.190
DO I even tell them
that Angie's dead?

13:47.493 --> 13:50.326
What if we never even
get out Of here?

13:52.540 --> 13:56.078
I mean, wouldn't it be better
if they just didn't know?

13:56.252 --> 13:59.335
If they're never gonna see her again
anyway.

14:02.300 --> 14:04.040
We'll figure it out, sweetie.

14:04.761 --> 14:05.796
[TABLET SLAMS]

14:10.641 --> 14:12.723
NORRIE:
Feel like checking your messages?

14:12.894 --> 14:14.600
There's only so much
fake-ass fan mail

14:14.771 --> 14:16.557
from wannabe dome-groupies
I can read

14:16.731 --> 14:19.393
before I barf all over
this wonderful piece Of machinery.

14:19.567 --> 14:22.058
- NO, thanks.
- We're stuck in here.

14:22.236 --> 14:25.478
What else are you are gonna do?
Build windmills?

14:35.124 --> 14:37.285
JUNIOR:
"I can help you, James."

14:57.188 --> 14:58.303
Jim.

14:58.481 --> 15:00.893
Respond if you're hearing this.

15:01.901 --> 15:02.981
That's the Killians' farm.

15:03.152 --> 15:04.653
- Here?
- There.

15:04.821 --> 15:06.436
There he is.

15:08.241 --> 15:10.732
Julia, wait here. Get the kit ready.

15:20.086 --> 15:21.622
BARBIE:
Jim. He's barely breathing.

15:21.796 --> 15:22.785
Let's get him up. Come on.

15:22.964 --> 15:24.420
It could be anaphylactic shock.

15:28.970 --> 15:29.959
[BOTTLES CLINKING]

15:32.056 --> 15:33.466
REBECCA:
Hey.

15:35.435 --> 15:36.470
Hey!

15:41.107 --> 15:42.938
Oh, hey.

15:45.820 --> 15:47.811
Guess you woke up.

15:50.825 --> 15:51.985
Where's Big Jim?

15:52.827 --> 15:54.818
Guess where I left him.

15:55.913 --> 15:57.494
What did you do tO him?

15:58.791 --> 15:59.826
He's gonna be tickled

16:00.001 --> 16:01.741
you're this concerned
with his well-being.

16:01.919 --> 16:04.205
What did you do?

16:04.380 --> 16:05.836
I didn't do anything.

16:06.007 --> 16:09.374
If he's righteous,
the rain will spare him.

16:11.679 --> 16:15.046
Thing is, I've known
that guy my whole life,

16:15.224 --> 16:17.340
and righteousness?

16:20.688 --> 16:25.022
That's not something that ranks high
on his list of attributes.

16:25.985 --> 16:28.067
Self-righteousness, yeah.

16:28.237 --> 16:31.024
Yeah, he's got that in spades.

16:31.199 --> 16:32.530
Listen.

16:33.409 --> 16:36.025
You have to let me out.

16:36.537 --> 16:38.198
This rain,

16:38.372 --> 16:40.829
I know how tO stop it
and nobody else will get hurt.

16:41.000 --> 16:45.209
If you untie me,
it'll be like you're helping me tO stop it.

16:46.380 --> 16:48.041
SO help me.

16:48.758 --> 16:50.043
Help me stop it, Lyle.

16:50.676 --> 16:54.294
Yeah, I--
I don't want tO stop the rain.

16:55.014 --> 16:56.845
And neither does the dome.

16:57.391 --> 16:58.892
The dome?

16:59.977 --> 17:02.059
The dome does not want.

17:02.230 --> 17:05.563
You know why Yahweh visited
the plagues on the Egyptians?

17:06.400 --> 17:10.860
TO demonstrate his awesome,
terrible power to non-believers.

17:11.948 --> 17:14.655
They were swallowed up
by the Red Sea.

17:14.825 --> 17:15.860
[CHUCKLES]

17:16.035 --> 17:17.536
Yeah.

17:19.413 --> 17:21.745
This isn't Yahweh.

17:23.209 --> 17:24.949
There's a new gOd in Chester's Mill.

17:25.586 --> 17:28.749
It surrounds and embraces us all.

17:29.757 --> 17:32.089
And it's gonna show no mercy
tO infidels.

17:33.636 --> 17:35.297
You got a choice, Rebecca.

17:37.640 --> 17:40.256
Ijust pray you make the right one.

17:52.572 --> 17:53.607
What happened tO him?

17:53.781 --> 17:56.568
He must've ingested
tOO much Of whatever's in that rain.

17:56.742 --> 17:58.824
- Hand me that pack.
BARBIE: Hold on, you put that in,

17:58.995 --> 18:03.204
he's not gonna be able tO talk.
Hey, what happened to Rebecca?

18:03.374 --> 18:05.239
Lyle.

18:05.918 --> 18:07.124
It was Lyle.

18:19.265 --> 18:20.596
What's that for?

18:21.183 --> 18:23.469
I don't wanna hurt you.

18:23.644 --> 18:26.260
But I can't have you
interfering with the plan.

18:26.439 --> 18:28.270
What plan?

18:28.441 --> 18:30.648
The End Of Days.

18:31.611 --> 18:33.272
After this rain stops,

18:34.155 --> 18:35.816
the rapture comes.

18:35.990 --> 18:38.447
True believers are gonna be reunited
in the hereafter.

18:41.078 --> 18:43.694
If you stop interfering with the plan,
I won't have to hurt you.

18:44.999 --> 18:46.284
I'll never stop.

18:47.752 --> 18:49.538
I'm sorry tO hear that, Rebecca.

18:50.588 --> 18:55.082
I indeed baptize you with water
unto repentance,

18:55.259 --> 18:58.843
but he that cometh after
is mightier than I.

18:59.013 --> 19:01.971
He shall baptize you
with the Holy Ghost...

19:04.226 --> 19:06.217
...and with fire.

19:21.869 --> 19:25.361
James. My love.

19:26.248 --> 19:28.204
My sweet son,

19:28.376 --> 19:30.867
by this time now,

19:31.045 --> 19:32.455
I expect you know,

19:32.630 --> 19:34.871
or have at least suspected
the truth.

19:35.383 --> 19:37.419
That I’m alive.

19:38.010 --> 19:43.300
lhope, I pray,
that you get this message.

19:44.433 --> 19:47.425
You must have
so many questions.

19:48.396 --> 19:52.139
And I know in my heart
that I will see you again.

19:52.566 --> 19:54.397
But in the meantime,

19:54.568 --> 19:56.183
if you need answers,

19:56.362 --> 19:58.899
talk to Lyle Chum/ey.

19:59.949 --> 20:01.735
James,

20:02.243 --> 20:03.608
this is important.

20:04.912 --> 20:06.777
Please listen.

20:07.289 --> 20:09.200
Talk to Lyle.

20:09.375 --> 20:12.333
Only to Lyle.

20:12.795 --> 20:14.205
And if my--

20:18.092 --> 20:19.548
NO, no, nO. Come on, come on.

20:19.719 --> 20:21.209
Joe, Joe, what happened?

20:21.387 --> 20:24.595
It's so strange.
Mine just did the same thing.

20:24.765 --> 20:26.380
We can't get access anywhere now.

20:26.559 --> 20:29.050
My tablet's working
and the signal's still coming through,

20:29.228 --> 20:31.264
but there seems to be
some kind Of block.

20:32.606 --> 20:35.439
- What are you doing?
JUNIOR: I gotta go find someone.

20:35.609 --> 20:37.224
Junior.

20:38.404 --> 20:41.862
NO, you can't gO outside.
It's dangerous.

20:42.992 --> 20:45.699
I always thought Lyle was harmless.

20:46.620 --> 20:49.111
Given the right circumstances,
anybody's capable Of anything.

20:49.915 --> 20:50.950
You really believe that?

20:51.125 --> 20:54.288
I believe that when things fall apart,
people show their true colors.

20:54.920 --> 20:56.626
SO, what, everyone's bad in the end?

20:56.797 --> 20:59.834
This is the perfect time tO be having
a debate over the nature Of man.

21:01.302 --> 21:02.667
These past few weeks,

21:02.845 --> 21:06.758
haven't you also seen people acting
selflessly, bravely?

21:06.932 --> 21:08.308
That's the exception to the rule.

21:08.476 --> 21:09.591
If this town's gonna survive,

21:09.769 --> 21:12.306
it's gonna need a firm hand
tO keep everybody in check.

21:13.898 --> 21:16.310
Like Big Jim's?

21:18.736 --> 21:19.976
BARBIE:
Julia, look at this.

21:24.408 --> 21:29.198
"Summer '88.
Lyle, Sam and Pauline."

21:40.007 --> 21:41.463
Sam? Sam, you there?

21:42.343 --> 21:43.378
I'm here, Julia.

21:43.552 --> 21:44.667
We're at Lyle's shop.

21:44.845 --> 21:47.632
He's not here,
but we found something.

21:47.807 --> 21:48.842
A photograph.

21:49.016 --> 21:50.005
SAM [OVER RADIO]:
Of what?

21:50.184 --> 21:54.143
You, Lyle and Pauline, in 1988.

21:54.313 --> 21:55.644
They're holding hands.

21:55.815 --> 21:58.898
Yeah, that's right around the time
he was seeing my sister.

21:59.944 --> 22:01.229
You never mentioned that.

22:01.403 --> 22:04.236
SAM: It was 25 years ago, Julia.
I didn't even think about it until now.

22:04.406 --> 22:06.863
And I haven't Spoken tO Lyle
since she died.

22:09.620 --> 22:11.736
Well, dO you have any idea
where he might be?

22:11.914 --> 22:13.370
Wish I did.

22:13.541 --> 22:14.656
If you find him, let me know.

22:14.834 --> 22:16.699
I got people tO tend tO here.

22:21.215 --> 22:22.330
What are you doing here?

22:22.508 --> 22:26.376
Heard you over the police radio.
I thought I'd help out.

22:26.554 --> 22:29.045
Great. Here, look at this.

22:29.223 --> 22:30.554
Any idea where this was taken?

22:30.724 --> 22:32.931
This is my mom
before she met my dad.

22:33.686 --> 22:35.142
Uh, it's by the cement factory.

22:35.312 --> 22:37.473
I used to build forts there
when I was a kid.

22:37.648 --> 22:41.061
Well, let's give it a shot.
See if Lyle tOOk her there.

22:41.235 --> 22:42.441
SO there's still a block?

22:42.611 --> 22:45.728
Yeah, we can't get access,
but the signal's still coming through.

22:45.906 --> 22:49.239
Maybe that means there must be,
I don't know, a crack.

22:49.410 --> 22:50.866
In the dome?

22:51.036 --> 22:53.493
Joe, they fired their biggest,
baddest bomb at it,

22:53.664 --> 22:55.120
and it didn't even make a dent.

22:55.291 --> 22:57.247
I don't mean, like, literally.

22:58.127 --> 23:01.369
What if the magnetism caused
some sort Of, I don't know, wormhole?

23:02.256 --> 23:04.497
All I'm saying is,
if we found the source Of this signal,

23:04.675 --> 23:05.755
we might find a way out.

23:07.261 --> 23:08.250
You wanna gO look?

23:11.390 --> 23:12.800
Come on.

23:22.902 --> 23:23.937
Why?

23:25.070 --> 23:26.105
Why'd I save you?

23:27.448 --> 23:28.938
I may not be on your team--

23:29.116 --> 23:31.949
Hell, I may even hate
your damn guts.

23:32.119 --> 23:34.451
--but that doesn't mean
I'm gonna let you die.

23:40.878 --> 23:43.039
At least not yet.

23:45.049 --> 23:46.789
Rest up, Jim.

23:52.431 --> 23:53.466
[SKIN SIZZLES,
THEN REBECCA SCREAMS]

23:53.641 --> 23:56.053
Stop! Stop. Wait, wait, wait. Please.

23:56.226 --> 23:58.057
LYLE:
Okay, Okay, all right.

23:58.228 --> 23:59.263
Okay.

23:59.438 --> 24:02.771
Are you willing tO accept
the grace Of repentance?

24:03.442 --> 24:05.273
I was wrong.

24:06.153 --> 24:08.895
The rain, it's a test.

24:09.448 --> 24:11.154
A test Of my worthiness.

24:11.325 --> 24:12.485
Whose test?

24:14.495 --> 24:16.110
The dome.

24:16.789 --> 24:18.871
I believe that now.

24:21.293 --> 24:23.124
Are you prepared tO surrender?

24:24.254 --> 24:28.213
Yes, yes. I believe in its plan. I do.

24:36.392 --> 24:38.974
NO, you only believe
in what you can see.

24:39.144 --> 24:40.520
Science.

24:43.691 --> 24:45.352
You're a lost cause.

24:51.907 --> 24:53.408
And now...

24:53.575 --> 24:54.860
NO, no, no. NO, don't. Don't.

24:55.035 --> 24:56.696
You're wasting my time.

24:58.539 --> 25:01.531
Drop it! Drop it! Put it on the ground!
Put it on the ground!

25:01.709 --> 25:04.121
Put your guns down!

25:04.545 --> 25:06.536
Put those guns on the ground.

25:06.714 --> 25:08.875
- Put it down.
- On the ground.

25:09.049 --> 25:12.382
Put the guns on the ground now.

25:12.553 --> 25:13.713
There you gO.

25:15.389 --> 25:17.550
Hey, I'll Shoot her right in front Of you.

25:18.851 --> 25:20.591
Now, put that down.

25:26.859 --> 25:28.645
That's right.

25:30.612 --> 25:33.103
Damn! What is wrong with you?

25:35.826 --> 25:36.941
JULIA:
Lyle?

25:39.371 --> 25:40.406
Please don't hurt her.

25:43.459 --> 25:46.792
You know this rain is here
tO rid this town Of non-believers.

25:47.755 --> 25:48.961
You know that.

25:49.590 --> 25:51.751
I heard you talking to those kids
at the diner.

25:52.843 --> 25:55.084
You believe. Don't you, lady?

25:55.262 --> 25:56.468
JULIA:
I do.

25:56.638 --> 25:58.924
But I believe the dome is here
tO protect us.

25:59.600 --> 26:00.931
Only the faithful.

26:01.101 --> 26:02.432
NO.

26:02.603 --> 26:03.592
All Of us.

26:07.775 --> 26:08.890
How do you know that?

26:09.818 --> 26:12.104
I know
because the dome spoke tO me.

26:13.280 --> 26:15.646
Maybe like it's spoken to you?

26:17.493 --> 26:21.577
Does the dome speak tO you, Lyle?

26:22.873 --> 26:24.488
NO.

26:24.708 --> 26:26.824
It doesn't Speak to me.

26:27.127 --> 26:31.120
It's a feeling directing my actions.

26:32.007 --> 26:33.463
Yeah, I understand.

26:35.469 --> 26:37.084
What did it say to you?

26:37.888 --> 26:41.255
It says if you want the darkness
tO abate,

26:41.475 --> 26:43.306
you must earn the light.

26:43.852 --> 26:44.967
Earn the light?

26:45.145 --> 26:48.308
Help me achieve
the dome's true plan.

26:50.609 --> 26:51.689
What is that?

26:51.860 --> 26:53.111
I mean, its true plan?

26:53.737 --> 26:55.193
JULIA:
I don't know.

26:55.906 --> 27:00.650
But I have faith that the answers
will be revealed.

27:03.330 --> 27:05.821
SO give me the gun now, Lyle.

27:13.966 --> 27:15.001
[LYLE SCREAMING]

27:18.345 --> 27:20.336
Why did you dO that?
He was about tO give in.

27:31.024 --> 27:34.152
- Signal's getting stronger.
-Joe.

27:45.205 --> 27:47.036
The source is coming
from down there.

27:47.207 --> 27:49.664
You don't have to gO.

27:59.511 --> 28:01.047
It's coming from here.

28:01.221 --> 28:04.179
Joe, don't be frightened.

28:04.349 --> 28:06.260
How about you don't tell him
how tO be?

28:06.935 --> 28:07.970
You're not his girlfriend,

28:08.145 --> 28:10.010
and as far as I know
you're not anyone.

28:13.817 --> 28:15.023
Let's just go.

28:22.284 --> 28:25.071
That locker was the last thing
that she touched.

28:26.246 --> 28:27.486
She died right here.

28:27.664 --> 28:29.950
And maybe
we Should just leave it alone.

28:30.125 --> 28:32.662
I have a bad feeling about this.

28:37.174 --> 28:38.710
GIRL:
Eight.

28:40.928 --> 28:42.464
Seventeen.

28:47.226 --> 28:48.261
One.

28:48.435 --> 28:49.424
[LOCK CLICKS]

29:23.262 --> 29:24.798
It's empty.

29:25.347 --> 29:27.258
Now the signal's gone.

29:29.351 --> 29:31.342
How did you know
that combination?

29:34.940 --> 29:36.931
Who the hell are you?

29:53.000 --> 29:54.035
REBECCA:
All right.

30:23.488 --> 30:25.945
It's Okay. Easy now.

30:26.283 --> 30:27.318
All right.

30:27.492 --> 30:28.527
Are you Okay?

30:28.702 --> 30:30.317
I'm fine.

30:33.707 --> 30:35.698
- Lyle?
- He's in jail.

30:36.251 --> 30:39.539
Trust me, he looks a lot worse
than we dO.

30:41.173 --> 30:43.038
The rain stopped.

30:43.633 --> 30:45.589
I stopped it.

30:45.844 --> 30:47.880
Not the dome. Me.

30:48.680 --> 30:49.715
How?

30:49.890 --> 30:52.222
A mixture Of salination
with some high-pH compounds.

30:53.602 --> 30:55.217
It's pretty science-y.

30:55.395 --> 30:58.057
I thought that stuff
didn't interest you.

31:00.067 --> 31:01.398
- It interests me.
- Good.

31:01.568 --> 31:05.402
Because I tOOk a tour Of the town
after the rain stopped.

31:07.324 --> 31:10.066
Our situation has only gotten worse.

31:10.535 --> 31:12.241
Some tough decisions
need to be made.

31:14.748 --> 31:16.033
What kind Of decisions?

31:18.627 --> 31:19.662
Listen, bitch,

31:19.836 --> 31:22.748
I am SO over this Little Miss Innocent
scam you're running.

31:22.923 --> 31:24.504
And we are not leaving

31:24.674 --> 31:27.416
until you come clean
about how you knew that combination,

31:27.594 --> 31:28.834
and why the Signal got blocked.

31:29.012 --> 31:30.172
I don't know.

31:30.347 --> 31:32.838
What are you, a safecracker?
A magician'S assistant?

31:33.016 --> 31:34.222
Because when we got here

31:34.768 --> 31:37.100
the locker was locked,
and then presto, change-O,

31:37.270 --> 31:38.305
you Opened it right up.

31:38.480 --> 31:39.811
Norrie, she doesn't know.

31:39.981 --> 31:43.223
It wasjust like I saw it in my head.

31:43.402 --> 31:46.064
In your head? In here?

31:46.238 --> 31:48.399
What else is in there?
IS your name in there?

31:48.573 --> 31:50.234
- Norrie, stop.
- NO!

31:50.409 --> 31:52.149
She just Shows up here
without any explanation

31:52.327 --> 31:54.864
on the day your Sister gets killed
in front Of that locker,

31:55.038 --> 31:57.495
and just happens to know
the combination?

31:57.666 --> 31:59.622
How did you know?

31:59.793 --> 32:01.749
- How did you know?
- Leave me alone!

32:01.920 --> 32:04.127
I'm telling the truth.

32:04.297 --> 32:07.084
- Why don't you trust her?
- She just saw it?

32:07.259 --> 32:10.592
That doesn't even make sense.
How do you see a combination?

32:10.762 --> 32:14.846
Actually, I think I might know.

32:16.935 --> 32:18.141
As I've been telling Jim,

32:18.311 --> 32:21.178
we have a serious resource crisis
tO deal with.

32:21.356 --> 32:23.267
I thought that that's what this whole

32:23.442 --> 32:25.307
registration drive
was about in the first place,

32:25.485 --> 32:26.895
is about how tO better allocate
them.

32:27.070 --> 32:30.187
Yes, but it's the lack Of resources
themselves

32:30.365 --> 32:31.480
that I'm most worried about.

32:31.658 --> 32:34.274
Even before today,
there were acute shortages.

32:34.453 --> 32:35.818
And after the rain?

32:35.996 --> 32:37.827
Far fewer medical supplies,

32:37.998 --> 32:39.329
crops destroyed,

32:39.499 --> 32:41.364
a considerable amount Of livestock
decimated,

32:41.543 --> 32:44.285
especially in the pig population.

32:46.006 --> 32:48.998
Day's coming when there won't be
enough food tO sustain us.

32:53.597 --> 32:56.509
SO we Should
have a contingency plan

32:56.683 --> 32:58.548
