33:05.525 --> 33:08.016
Selectively, I'm saying.

33:08.195 --> 33:09.184
--tO thin the herd.

33:10.447 --> 33:12.028
Selectively?

33:24.878 --> 33:26.368
The questions on your form:

33:26.880 --> 33:30.043
family background,
history Of illness.

33:30.217 --> 33:35.507
This is a census to help you decide
who lives and who dies.

33:35.680 --> 33:36.715
Let's get out Of here.

33:46.441 --> 33:49.057
She's just talking
about a contingency.

33:59.829 --> 34:01.239
Trouble in paradise?

34:01.414 --> 34:02.915
BARBIE:
Julia.

34:03.083 --> 34:04.289
Listen, you don't understand.

34:04.459 --> 34:06.575
I understand you're taking their Side.

34:06.753 --> 34:08.664
NO,nO,nO.
I'm not taking anyone's side here.

34:08.838 --> 34:10.578
I'm trying to consider
every possible Option.

34:10.757 --> 34:13.590
You said, "When things fall apart,
people Show their true colors."

34:13.760 --> 34:14.875
Are these yours?

34:15.595 --> 34:17.881
I need tO know that you will stand
with me against them,

34:18.056 --> 34:19.557
against that.

34:19.724 --> 34:21.885
They don't get to throw
anybody out of the life boat.

34:22.060 --> 34:25.598
- What if it's Sinking?
- I believe we will find a way.

34:25.772 --> 34:27.558
Belief only gets you SO far.

34:28.775 --> 34:31.812
I thought I knew you. I was wrong.

34:33.113 --> 34:34.944
Don't follow me.

34:39.452 --> 34:42.285
LYLE [SINGING]:
Long as I remember

34:43.123 --> 34:48.834
The rain '3 been coming down

34:49.004 --> 34:54.465
Clouds of mystery pouring confusion

34:54.634 --> 34:57.296
On the ground

34:58.138 --> 35:01.471
Getting through the ages

35:01.641 --> 35:05.475
Trying to ﬁnd the sun

35:06.688 --> 35:09.475
And I wonder, still I wonder

35:09.649 --> 35:13.141
Who'll stop the rain

35:20.785 --> 35:22.446
I was wondering
when you'd Show up.

35:22.954 --> 35:25.946
Aren't you afraid
Of people seeing us together?

35:27.709 --> 35:29.574
Building's empty.

35:30.712 --> 35:33.169
I could kill you and nobody'd know.

35:35.008 --> 35:36.339
Nobody'd care.

35:37.010 --> 35:38.295
Maybe.

35:39.220 --> 35:40.630
But you won't.

35:42.182 --> 35:44.298
When this thing came down,

35:44.768 --> 35:46.850
I told you to lay low.

35:47.103 --> 35:48.218
Follow my lead.

35:49.272 --> 35:50.307
I got a new leader.

35:50.482 --> 35:51.688
You made a promise,

35:51.858 --> 35:55.976
25 years ago, tO make sure
that what we buried stayed buried.

35:57.113 --> 35:58.853
You've heard Of force majeure,
yeah?

36:01.826 --> 36:06.320
Extraordinary circumstance
that frees both parties from a contract.

36:06.498 --> 36:08.159
But you know what?

36:08.333 --> 36:12.042
This dome is about as majeure a force
as it gets.

36:15.048 --> 36:17.255
But it's gonna deliver us
tO a better place.

36:17.425 --> 36:19.837
I'm afraid you got that
exactly backward, pal.

36:24.724 --> 36:27.966
I grow weary Of this conversation.

36:28.144 --> 36:30.886
See you on the other side, Sammy.

36:42.075 --> 36:44.111
REBECCA:
I read about a tribe in Borneo.

36:44.285 --> 36:46.367
I can't remember
what they're called.

36:46.538 --> 36:48.244
But they had this ritual,

36:48.415 --> 36:50.451
something that they would do
every year.

36:50.625 --> 36:54.368
They'd put all their elderly,
their infirm, up into a tree

36:54.546 --> 36:55.911
and they would Shake it.

36:56.089 --> 36:59.957
And whoever held on
was considered strong enough,

37:00.135 --> 37:02.547
useful enough,
tO make it tO the next year.

37:04.431 --> 37:05.967
And those who couldn't hold on?

37:07.517 --> 37:08.882
LOOk.

37:10.603 --> 37:11.888
When I said

37:12.063 --> 37:13.928
the day was coming
we wouldn't have provisions

37:14.107 --> 37:16.644
